# UI Design System Enforcement (STRICT)

This repository uses a stabilized design system (ds-* / dash-*).

All UI changes MUST follow these rules.

## 1. Reuse First (Mandatory)
Always reuse existing:
- ds-* classes
- dash-* classes
- design tokens

Before editing:
- Identify the exact DS component being reused

## 2. Minimal Diff Only
- Only fix the requested issue
- No layout restructuring
- No redesign
- No global visual changes

## 3. No New Styling Patterns
STRICTLY FORBIDDEN:
- raw Tailwind zinc-* / blue-* utilities in templates
- one-off styling
- inline Tailwind clutter
- parallel component systems

## 4. Scope Lock
- Only modify the requested file/component
- Do not touch shared/global files unless explicitly requested

## 5. Design System Integrity
- Do not extend DS unless explicitly requested
- Do not override DS behavior with ad-hoc styles

## 6. Failure Conditions
A change is invalid if:
- it introduces new styling patterns
- it bypasses ds-* / dash-* system
- it modifies unrelated files
- it changes global UI unintentionally